# Niagara System: Forest Ambience
# Creates the base atmospheric tension through subtle environmental VFX

## EMITTER 1: Dust Motes (Sunlight Shafts)
- Spawn Rate: 50-80 particles/second
- Lifetime: 8-12 seconds
- Size: 0.1-0.3 world units
- Velocity: Gentle upward drift (0.5-1.5 m/s)
- Color: Warm amber (255,220,180) with 30% alpha
- Material: M_DustMote_Translucent

### Behavior Modules:
- Initial Location: Box spawn within light shaft volumes
- Velocity Inheritance: Wind system integration
- Size Over Life: Slight growth then fade
- Color Over Life: Fade to transparency
- Collision: Simple world collision with bounce

## EMITTER 2: Floating Spores
- Spawn Rate: 20-30 particles/second  
- Lifetime: 15-25 seconds
- Size: 0.2-0.8 world units
- Velocity: Slow random drift with wind influence
- Color: Subtle green-yellow (200,255,180) with 20% alpha
- Material: M_Spore_Organic

### Behavior Modules:
- Initial Location: Random distribution in forest canopy
- Curl Noise Force: Organic floating movement
- Gravity Scale: -0.1 (slight upward tendency)
- Rotation: Slow random tumble

## EMITTER 3: Micro Leaf Particles
- Spawn Rate: 10-15 particles/second
- Lifetime: 20-30 seconds  
- Size: 0.5-1.2 world units
- Velocity: Gentle falling with wind gusts
- Color: Forest green variations (120,180,100)
- Material: M_LeafFragment_Opaque

### Behavior Modules:
- Initial Location: Tree branch positions
- Wind Force: Strong influence from weather system
- Collision: Ground collision with settle behavior
- Mesh Renderer: Small leaf geometry variations

## SYSTEM PARAMETERS (Exposed for Level Design):
- Density_Multiplier: 0.5-2.0 (adjusts all spawn rates)
- Wind_Strength: 0.0-3.0 (affects all particle movement)
- Sunlight_Intensity: 0.0-1.0 (controls dust mote visibility)
- Atmosphere_Tint: Color picker (overall color influence)